strings : countWords

Write a method named countWords that accepts a string as its parameter and returns the number of words in it. 
A word is a sequence of one or more non-space characters. For example, the call of countWords("What is your name?") should return 4.

   public static int countWords(String str) {
        int count = 0;
        str = str.trim();
        if (str.isEmpty()) {
            return count;
        }
        count++;
        for (int i = 0; i < str.length() - 1; i++) {
            if (str.charAt(i) == ' ' && str.charAt(i + 1) != ' ')
                count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
